"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d90153",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Streptococcus pneumoniae"
]
},
" is the most commonly identified bacterial cause of ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"community-acquired pneumonia",
"children":[
"CAP"
]
},
" in patients of all ages. CAP caused by ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Moraxella"
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Haemophilus"
]
},
" species occurs mainly in patients with chronic pulmonary disease. Atypical microorganisms that cause CAP include ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Mycoplasma pneumoniae"
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Chlamydophila pneumoniae"
]
},
" and are more common in persons aged 20 to 40 years."
]
}
]
},
