"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"a"
]
},
"PSI Step 1 Screen: If no factors are present, patient is assigned risk class I and can likely be managed as an outpatient. Patients with at least one risk factor are stratified by a more complex Step 2 scale (not shown) into risk class II-V."
],
[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"b"
]
},
"IDSA/ATS Criteria for Defining Severe CAP: Patients with 1 major criterion have severe CAP and are best managed in the ICU. Consideration of minor criteria, along with clinical judgment, is recommended to guide the need for higher levels of care."
]
]
